        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 1:55PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 155 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ashville, or 9 miles northeast of Springville, moving southeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Oneonta, Springville, Odenville, Margaret, Ashville, Ragland,
Allgood, Branchville, Inland Lake, Highland Lake, Whitney Junction,
St. Clair Springs, Wattsville, Holly Springs, Caldwell, Horse Pens
Forty, and I 59 Rest Areas At Oneonta.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
